Google was co-founded by [[Larry Page]] and [[Sergey Brin (immigrant from Russia)]] while they were students at [[Stanford University]] and the company was first incorporated as a [[privately held company]] on [[September 7]], [[1998]]. Google's [[initial public offering]] took place on [[August 19]], [[2004]], raising [[United States dollar|US$]]1.67 billion, making it worth US$23 billion. Through a series of new product developments, acquisitions and partnerships, the company has expanded its initial [[google search|search]] and [[AdWords|advertising]] business into other areas, including [[Gmail|web-based e-mail]], [[Google Earth|online mapping]], [[Google Docs|office productivity]], and [[YouTube|video sharing]], among others.
In 2006, "google" came in second on [[Merriam-Webster's Words of the Year]]<ref>[http://www.m-w.com/info/07words_prev.htm Merriam-Webster's webpage] Retrieved on [[December 30]], [[2007]]</ref>.
